ðŸ“Š DBMS vs RDBMS Summary Table
===========================================================================================================================================
| Feature               |   DBMS                                               |   RDBMS                                                 |
| --------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Full Form**         | Database Management System                           | Relational Database Management System                   |
| **Examples**          | Normal File System, XML, etc.                        | MySQL, Oracle, SQL Server, MongoDB, etc.                |
| **Data Storage**      | Data stored in files without relationships           | Data stored in tabular format (tables with relations)   |
| **Data Access**       | One user can access data at a time                   | Multiple users can access data concurrently             |
| **Data Structure**    | Custom or hierarchical data structures               | Uses relational (tabular) structure                     |
| **Query Language**    | No standard query language                           | Uses SQL to manage and retrieve data                    |
| **Scalability**       | Small data, less scalable                            | Large data, highly scalable                             |
| **Backup & Recovery** | Hard to manage backups                               | Easy backup and recovery mechanisms                     |
| **Security**          | Less secure                                          | More secure and controlled access                       |
| **Normalization**     | Not supported; leads to redundancy and inconsistency | Fully supported; ensures data integrity and consistency |
| **Ease of Use**       | Hard to deal with                                    | Easy to work with and manage                            |
| **Data Sharing**      | Limited or manual                                    | Centralized and efficient data sharing                  |
===========================================================================================================================================
